issue.title: Qute: fix regression in perf optimization of ReflectionValueResolver

body:
Ok, found it. It's a regression caused by https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/pull/43308.

I've sent a PR with a fix. This is the fix: https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/pull/44817/files#diff-172c5b92001e43b2cc32c9a8025b0730084d360fa398a1600dc4e4a8b88cc3d3R65 ðŸ¤¦ ðŸ˜¦ 

Workarounds exists: do not use the reflection fallback value resolver, but instead:

-  use type-safe templates/records/expressions (e.g. https://quarkus.io/guides/qute-reference#template-records)
- annotate the `ProjectSchedules` class with [`@TemplateData`](https://quarkus.io/guides/qute-reference#template_data)

Hi @mkouba , thanks.
Adding `@TemplateData` made it work again.
Regards,
Martin.
